race.comment: CAMBRIDGE BAY (1) is unlucky to still be a maiden placing in all three outings last preparation and strikes a very winnable contest here. Hoop Du Plessis has been in the stirrups for all four career starts and sticks today. Will be right there at the business end. RATENOTICE (15) didn't handle the step-up in trip last time out but go on the solid second over this track and trip two back. Worth another chance. CLIODHNA MAEVE (7) has hit the top-five in ten of her past 11 starts and looks to be building up to a maiden win. Sure to give this a mighty shake. ISLA DELILAH (13) good effort on debut last start when she hit the line hard to finish fifth at Sunshine Coast over 1200m. Plenty of scope for improvement and worth watching for any market confidence.
